               <head>Treatise on Sufism by the Makhdum Jahaniyan Jahan Gasht</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Sirāj al-hidāyah by Makhdūm Jahāniyān Jahān Gasht, Jalāl al-Dīn, -1383</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1038-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_91095241">Makhdūm Jahāniyān Jahān Gasht, Jalāl al-Dīn, -1383</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_91095241">ابو عبد الله جلال الدّين حسين ابن احمد ابن حسين البخارى الحسينى مخدوم جهانيان جهان گشت </persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22195">Sirāj al-hidāyah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22195">سراج الهداية</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Fragment of a treatise by the Ṣūfī saint, <persName key="person_91095241" role="aut">Abū ʿAbd Allāh Jalāl al-Dīn Ḥusayn ibn Aḥmad ibn Ḥusayn al-Bukhārī al-Ḥusaynī</persName>, known as the <persName key="person_91095241" role="aut">Makhdūm Jahāniyān Jahān Gasht</persName> (d. 785/1384), dealing with broad aspects of theology, ritual, jurisprudence, literature, and dietetics. 

                        </p>
                        <p>The work consists of nine bāb. 
</p>
                        <p>Defective at beginning. 
</p>
                        <p>Order of folios is somewhat confused. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 183r): completed midday on Sunday, 6 Z̲ū al-Qaʿdah 1130/1 October 1718. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
